Core Message
Anticipate and block procedural attacks before they happen.

Lesson Introduction
Firewalls in litigation are protective strategies that prevent loss from a single point of failure.

Teaching Block
	1.	Identify Threats â€“ Missed deadlines, jurisdictional attacks.
	2.	Build Redundancy â€“ Backup arguments and filings.
	3.	Update Regularly â€“ Adjust firewall as case evolves.

Real-World Illustration
